      "message": "Unfortunately this is not possible until we get rid of the globs. If we merge both functions now, globs will start to be used as part of the loop in function hasRef below and will match grandchildren refs too, i.e. we need to include grandchildren when matching regexp, but need to exclude them while matching globs. Once support for globs is removed, we\u0027ll be able to merge matchRef into hasSuffix and we can even do that with a switch like this:\n\n  switch {\n  case suffix \u003d\u003d \"*\":\n    panic(fmt.Errorf(\"watchedRefNamespace membership should only be checked for refs, not ref glob %s\", suffix))\n  case w.allChildren:\n    return true\n  case w.childRegexp !\u003d nil \u0026\u0026 w.childRegexp.MatchString(suffix):\n    return true\n  case w.someChildren \u003d\u003d nil:\n    return false\n  default:\n    return w.someChildren.Has(suffix)\n  }\n\nI\u0027ll add a TODO to do that after deprecating globsl",
